args:
The castle is abuzz with excitement thanks to
the New Year's party, during which the winner
of the hospitality face-off becomes a hot topic.
When the prince recommends a draw, Botan
and the other Hinomotoans accept, after which
the party continues long into the night.
The mochi is ready, everyone.\nPlease help yourselves.
Me and Ranzal pounded it, so eat up!
Do be careful not to burn yourself.\nIt's freshly made, after all.
Your cooking really is the best, Sazanka.
This flavor sure takes me backâ€”it's what\nNew Year's is all about!
I'm beginning to wonder if your entire\nreason for tracking me down was simply\nto enjoy Sazanka's cooking.
I'm convinced there's nothing that Sazanka\ncan't turn into a feast.
That means something from you, Cleo.
Your words flatter me. If there is anything\non the menu that you're curious about,\nI'd be happy to share my techniques.
In that case, show me everything.
After the party, she means. ...I think.
Right then! Might someone be willing\nto teach me how to play this game?\nI believe it is called ï¼‚hanetsuki,ï¼‚ yes?
The decorations on this paddle are\nso cute, it made me curious to try it.
I'll be happy to show you the ropesâ€”\nbut if you lose, I get to smear ink\nall over your face!
Is that actually part of the rules?!\nMost games I'm familiar with don't\nhave such punishments built in.
It's not just punishmentâ€”the ink is used\nto ward off evil spirits.
Regardless, to be besmeared with ink...
Well, just don't lose, then! I'm not worried.\nHeck, I mastered that spinning ï¼‚komaï¼‚ top\nthingy just fine.
Such overconfidence will likely end with\nyou covered head to toe in ink, Luca.
You think the master of sylvan games is\ngonna lose? Not happening!
Since when does ANYONE call you that?
Since I decided it just now! Anyway,\nI'm taking home the win for sure.
Speakin' of which, who ended up winnin'\nthat hospitality face-off?
I believe Ieyasu's team is leading by a\nscore of two to one.
Interesting. I thought you'd put up more\nof a fight over your loss.
Yeah, but I sort of interfered with Ieyasu\nand caused a whole bunch of trouble,\nand they STILL came out on top.
What can I say? The Twelve Wyrmclans\njust know how to be hospitable.
Alas, I fear my hospitality was insufficient.
I forgot the most important point:\nthat the one offering hospitality\nshould also enjoy themselves.
Yeah, but all the Alberian folks had\na GREAT time!
If one offers hospitality in name only,\nthere is no point to any of it.
Rrrgh! You are SO thickheaded!\nI lost, okay? Deal with it!
How can you fight on a day like this?!\nBad humans! Bad!
Hey, I'm just going out of my way to\nbe a grateful loser!
Ieyasu here is the bonehead who\nwon't accept it.
It's just strange that youâ€”perhaps the\nworst loser I knowâ€”would be so\ncompromising in this.
It reminds me of how we used to bicker\namongst ourselves as children.
Yeah, because you've got a thick skull!
Oh, I think you could give me a run for my\nmoney in that department.
Look, we all had an amazing time thanks\nto you folks.
And right now, everyone is happyâ€”\nincluding the two of you.
So why do we have to pick a winner?
Hmm... I suppose there is truth to that.
As a person who brings good fortune,\nI neglected something important.
In Hinomoto, we've a proverb that states,\nï¼‚Good fortune will come to the home \nof those who smile.ï¼‚
I have always tried to bear this in mind.
And yet, I thought so heavily of my duty\nthat I neglected my own feelings.
It is meaningless to bring fortune and\nhappiness to another if you do not\nfirst possess it yourself.
I am grateful to you for making me recall\nwhat it means to share joy with another.
No, it's us who should be thanking you\nfor bringing such a fun-filled New Year's\nto our doorstep.
But that being said, what do you all\nplan to do now?
We shall continue visiting various\ncountries before returning home.
I understandâ€”although it makes me sad\nto think of you leaving.
I am grateful that you regret our parting.
Still, I hope this is but the beginning\nof a long and fruitful relationship.
Though the distance between Hinomoto\nand Alberia is great, we shall ever come\nto your aid in times of trouble.
And don't you fret! Even if this big lug goes\nhome, I'm stayin' with you guys.
It's irritating that Ieyasu saw me as so\nweak that he couldn't tell me the truth.
So I'm gonna stay around here for a while\nand train up.
You mean here in the castle?!
You know it!, Er, I mean, if that's okay\nwith you, {player_name}?
Botan, you mustn't declare such a thing\nwithout asking permission first.
It's no problem, Botan. Welcome aboard.
Ha! I'm gonna get so insanely strong\nmy muscles will have muscles!
Then I can return home to serve my\nmaster and future shogun.
A very promising decision, Botan.\nI shall await your return.
Aw, poo! My mochi got cold!
Bwaaa ha ha! That'll teach ya to make\na big speech when there's food waitin'!
On that note, let us put aside these\ndiscussions for the nonce...
(ï¼‚Good fortune will come to the home \nof those who smile,ï¼‚ eh?)
(Well, I know we'll have some hard times\nin the new year, but we're going to\novercome them together.)
